<item>
            <title>[LU-6656] Non atomic allocation under spin lock in qmt_glimpse_lock</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6656</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In qmt_glimpse_lock:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While the resource lock (a spin lock) is held, it does&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OBD_ALLOC_PTR(work);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This allocation is not atomic, so it can potentially sleep.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sleeping with a spinlock held is not a good idea in general, and (per Andreas) it is specifically not allowed for GFP_NOFS allocations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
